div.h2: Segment Selector GDT Linear Address Resolution

p.em: data_walk: how CS=0x08 and CS=0x1B are decoded by the CPU on every memory access

g.text: GDTR Register (6 bytes, loaded by lgdt)
GDT in Memory (40 bytes = 5 x 8-byte descriptors)
Hardware Access Check: max(CPL, RPL) <= DPL
Next stage: Paging (CR3 -> Page Directory -> Physical)

div.p: Bits 47-16 : Base = 0xC0105000 (kernel virt addr of GDT array) Bits 15-0 : Limit = 0x0027 (5 entries x 8 bytes - 1 = 39) CPU uses: physical_entry = GDTR.Base + (Index x 8)

tr.td: RPL=3 added by selector (e.g. 0x18 base index OR 3 = 0x1B)

p.strong: Three privilege fields compared on every segment load:

tr.td: Required privilege to access this segment
Rule: max(CPL, RPL) <= DPL must be true, else #GP (General Protection Fault)

ul.li: Ring 0 code loads DS=0x10 (DPL=0): max(0,0)=0 <= 0 OK
Ring 3 code loads DS=0x23 (DPL=3): max(3,3)=3 <= 3 OK

div.p: Segmentation produces a linear address. With the flat model (Base=0), linear = logical offset. The MMU then applies paging: linear[31:22] -> Page Directory index linear[21:12] -> Page Table index linear[11:0] -> 4 KB page offset Physical = PTE.frame_addr OR offset Paging also re-checks the U/S bit per page:

ul.li: U/S=0 and CPL=3 causes #PF (page fault, protection violation) This is why ring-3 processes cannot read kernel pages even though GDT segments span the full 4 GB.

div.p: Byte layout (8 bytes / 64 bits) Byte 7 Base[31:24] = 0x00 Byte 6 Flags+Lim = 0xCF G=1,D=1,L=0 Byte 5 Access = 0x9A P=1,DPL=00,S=1,E=1,R=1 Byte 4 Base[23:16] = 0x00 Byte 3 Base[15:8] = 0x00 Byte 2 Base[7:0] = 0x00 Bytes 1-0 Limit[15:0] = 0xFFFF Base = 0x00000000 Limit = 0xFFFFF x 4KB = 4 GB DPL = 0 (ring 0 only)
Linear = Base + Logical Offset 0x00000000 + offset = offset Flat model: linear = logical Paging then maps linear to physical CPL = 0 (ring 0 enforced in CS)

Byte layout (8 bytes / 64 bits) Byte 7 Base[31:24] = 0x00 Byte 6 Flags+Lim = 0xCF G=1,D=1,L=0 Byte 5 Access = 0xFA P=1,DPL=11,S=1,E=1,R=1 Byte 4 Base[23:16] = 0x00 Byte 3 Base[15:8] = 0x00 Byte 2 Base[7:0] = 0x00 Bytes 1-0 Limit[15:0] = 0xFFFF Base = 0x00000000 Limit = 0xFFFFF x 4KB = 4 GB DPL = 3 (ring 3 required)
Linear = Base + Logical Offset 0x00000000 + offset = offset Flat model: linear = logical Paging enforces U/S bit per page CPL = 3 (ring 3 enforced in CS) Kernel pages (U/S=0) cause #PF on access
